meanings.definition: An Irish surname, Anglicized from Ó Cinnéide.
meanings.english_definition: An Irish surname, Anglicized from Ó Cinnéide.

meanings.definition: Arthur Edwin Kennelly (1861–1939), an American electrical engineer.
meanings.english_definition: Arthur Edwin Kennelly (1861–1939), an American electrical engineer.

etymology.value: The surname is derived from the Irish Ó Cinnéide, meaning descendant of Cinnéide.
